                <p><strong>February 19, 2027:</strong> Distance 0.68 AU, magnitude -1.2, diameter 13.8". Aphelic opposition—Mars at minimum brightness/size. Located in Leo. This represents the least impressive Mars opposition of the 15-year cycle. Still easily visible but don't expect dramatic brilliance.</p>

